I am so honored that our magical day 8.22.22 where together before God and loved ones we pledged our vows to love each other forsaking all others in a covenant marriage—was featured as an editorial on @the_reflective_ 🤍 

Our wedding was no doubt a festive—beautiful affair forever engraned in me. My dream day with no shortage of flowers, food, fashion, faith or merriment. A big thank you to all those who made it such—especially my wonderful parents. I honor you both.  But more it was the day I made a commitment before God to love my husband no matter the circumstance until death do us part. I've learned a thing or two about those vows since being married. I can honestly say I have understood the brevity of my commitment more today than I did that day—as most wives would agree as you've journeyed through the trials of life. I am thankful to have Jesus guiding me each day as I strive to honor those vows. 
 
I love my husband more today than I did on 8.22.22 and it is my heart that unto God submitted solely to each other —forsaking all others, together there is nothing we can not do. 🤍 

I have always been a blessed girl with the favor of God and today is no different. All that I am, have, do and will do is unto Jesus. 

Thank you @the_reflective_ I do not take this lightly. I admire your vision and wholeheartedly say follow @the_reflective_ they have done and will continue to do BIG things in the fashion community. It's a must follow for ALL gals not just those who choose modesty. 

Read the full story here: https://the-reflective.com/blogs/posts/modest-fashion-blogger-alexa-sue-anne-weds-in-avante-garde-bespoke-empire-waist-gown

If I could provide an iota of wisdom to the gals—waiting for their husband, are about to wed or are dreaming of their wedding... 

1. Don't take this decision lightly it is the biggest choice you will make in your lifetime outside of choosing to follow Jesus. Tread with EXTREME CAUTION. Fast, pray and then pray some more. PRE-MARITAL & POST MARRIAGE COUNSELING, INDIVIDUAL COUNSELING

2. Keep Jesus at the center of your marriage. Do not trust those outside your marriage easily and protect who speaks into your marriage at all cost. Use discernment... “What God puts together LET NO MAN put ASUNDER.” That means let no one or no thing SEPARATE you from your spouse. 

3. Get some thick skin sis—marriage is hard work. You vowed to stand in the gap for your spouse no matter what. Prayer needs to be a 24/7 situation. Faith is a key ingredient & baby some things take time. Are you ready to break generational curses? Are you ready to WAR? 

4. The wedding is a day. The marriage is a lifetime. Invest accordingly. 

5. Don't compare to little Susie or Johnny it will only cause TROUBLE. In any category. 

6. How you love your spouse indicates how you love Jesus. As much as you love your spouse is as much as you love Jesus. What you do unto your spouse is what you do unto Jesus. 

7. “To love someone long-term is to attend a thousand funerals of the people they used to be.” So be ready— you are going to change and so is he. 

8. Submission to God is the most important. Then submission to your spouse and that is both parties submitting one to another. Don't get it twisted or cherry pick. 

9. Speak truth in love. Have boundries. Protect your marriage. If they don’t like your spouse YOU DON’T LIKE THEM. 

10. Order of the family/life: GOD, SPOUSE, CHILDREN, FAMILY, FRIENDS, JOB | Do not put anything before your spouse not even the church/pastor. 

11. “A handsome man and a pretty woman will make a beautiful wedding. But a RIGHTEOUS MAN and A VIRTUOUS WOMAN will make a BEAUTIFUL MARRIAGE.”

12. Learn these scriptures by heart. 1 Corinthians 13:4-7, Hebrews 13:4, Ecclesiastes 4:9-12, Mark 8-12, Genesis 2:23, 24, Ephesians 5:22-33, Proverbs 18: 22

When you know with your entire being that no matter the final outcome and no matter what trial each day brings that Jesus holds your future—you’ll be filled with joy, peace and rest like you’ve never felt in your life. 🩷 #peacethatmakesnosense

To be a good father is to assume one of the greatest responsibilities in this life. Your children but also to the mother of your children. Your example is learned in the home. The best news is that it is also never to late to rise to the occasion— 

Happy Father’s Day to the men in my life. 🤍  I pray every day that God would give you the strength and wisdom needed for the role you have. It is so very important. 

To my daddy. I love you and am so thankful for the restoration I have seen God do in our relationship. I have no greater JOY than to see you pursuing the heart of Jesus and loving mom like Christ loves the church. It gives me hope and is a prayer I have prayed continuously since I was a little girl. Thank you for the most beautiful wedding and for always being there when I need you. You work so hard and I admire the work ethic you have to get things you put your mind to done. I love having fun with you on whatever cool toy you’ve brought home—those are some of my favorite memories together. I appreciate you dad more than you know. I look forward to one day seeing you become a grandpa to my babies. With God truly first I can’t wait to see all the blessings we will share in the coming years! 

To my second father and pastor of many years. Thank you for being a Shepard in my life and another father figure. No doubt God knew I would need you in my life and I am thankful for role you play in so many lives. Your example is one that is SO needed. I love how you love Gods children with such care and the most wonderful lady sis Joy. Your marriage is a wonderful biblical example. I miss you both! 

To my father in law. Thank you for the investment you have already made in my life. You’ve always been fun to be around! I love and appreciate you. I pray God’s favor and blessings over you. I love to see how you put your family first and treat the plant queen with the love she deserves! Thank you for all you do. 

To my Heavenly Father—wow. What a blessing it is to be a daughter of the KING. I’m not ever worried about a thing because you take care of your children and I’m one of your children. You’ve never let me down and you won’t ever. 😭

When gratitude becomes your default setting, life changes. 🤌🏻 Out here fully functioning on JESUS joy & JESUS joy alone. ❤️‍🩹

3rd pic=my whole heart bursting, ifykyk 🥹

#nayc23 #jesusjoy #glory #blessedbethenameofthelord #john137
It’s giving ✨truth✨ & ✨coastal Christian girl ✨ 🦪 #john137

Happy birthday to my favorite person in the world. My baby brother, built in bestie & our family’s glue. Your character surpasses that of the greatest. I love you & pray all the favor + blessings of God over your life. His will for you is going to blow your mind… keep serving him. Love you SHUG.
She is more precious than rubies; nothing you desire can compare with her. Proverbs 3:15 ❤️‍🩹 #john137

Happy birthday daddy!! I love you. Thank you for giving me my dream wedding—truly the most beautiful celebration. Thank you for being a support through tough times. I can’t wait to celebrate with you soon!! 🍰🧡

Happy anniversary to my precious parents. 🤍 You have shown me that if it truly is love—as his word commands that it won’t fail. Love extends beyond a feeling but is a choice you bear daily. You choose to love your spouse even in the hardest of circumstances. You have been a beautiful example of covenant marriage. I love you both and I am thankful you’re my parents. I have seen you overcome challenge and I will forever know in marriage if you’re truly committed it's not IF but HOW. 

I know you never got to have your own—I truly treasure the beautiful wedding celebration you gave me. Thank you for your investment into my special day and into the gal I am. I am blessed beyond measure. #vowingviloria 

Momma you’ll forever be dad’s uptown girl. 🤌🏻

So blessed I could celebrate my beautiful friend and her expected little rooster. She will make the most amazing mom & it is my utter delight to share in this new life! Auntie Lex is on deck when needed! I love you P! So proud of you. 

🩵🚜🐔 Thank you to the Walters family for always being such gracious hosts. I love seeing you all. 

P.S. what even is this song & how could I NOT use it?!

8.22.22 I may never understand this earth side but when you’ve done all you can do to stand at some point you have to release it to Jesus. He holds my broken heart and my future in the palms of his hands. I am loved by my father in heaven. He will never betray, abandon or reject me—he says nothing you desire can compare with me. To all the little girls and big girls watching who experience physically devastating and heartbreaking betrayal Jesus is the comforter. He has carried me this entire year. Thank you to all the wonderful people who shared in our wedding day. Thank you to my parents beyond words, the couple who purchased our flights and my in-laws for our honeymoon.  I will never forget those treasured memories. I am not ready to delete a chapter that played such a big role in my life and rather than deleting my profile like most would in this situation I feel a responsibility to be authentic. I want this tragedy to be a living testimony. Nothing is guaranteed and life is filled with hard moments. And to everyone who watches my life: don’t give up. Season 2 God spoke to me John 17:3🤍 To the countless people who have prayed, held me up, offered us counseling—your love will never be forgotten. 

God sees our brokenness and gives it meaning. He sees our pain and gives it purpose. He sees our wait and gives it reason. And He sees our future and gives it promise.
#transparency #beytrayl  #rejection  #heartbreak #abandonment 
#isaiah354 #john173 

Please pray with me that this vulnerability will be a help to someone and that God will protect my heart. Please ask that he bless this effort to be authentic. @thekingwillcomemusic

Choosing forgiveness over bitterness, has been a profound lesson in my life. It has taught me the power of compassion, the freedom of letting go, and the healing that forgiveness brings through Jesus. Embracing forgiveness has not only lightened my heart but also radically intensified my JOY and allowed me to move forward with grace and love. Perspective through Christ says “count it all joy” and find your gratitude even in heartache. You can't control the outcomes of most things in life, or expect others to do right but you can CHOOSE to walk in forgiveness and set yourself free from bondage knowing Jesus sees all. The true test of Christianity is in how you love the Judas in your life. ❤️‍🩹
 
#forgiveness #betrayal #churchhurt #spiritualabuse #cultawareness  #divorce #abandoned  #healing #jesusjoy #christianity #love

Girls, swipe for the secret sauce of life 🤍

Your most effective ministry will yield from your deepest hurts. We must also remember our God will never allow pain without purpose. We are not promised it will ever be easy but yet he does promise he will never leave us in our pain. He always welcomes a heavy heart at his feet. There is no time limit on how long he will welcome your burdens. He made you and wants to hear from you in relationship with him in both the pain + the joyful moments. 🤍

To the girls I speak with on the daily, keep pressing in. We will endure for the greater purpose of bringing glory to HIS name. Use your pain to cultivate a deeper relationship with Jesus. 

#faith #pain #heartbreak #purpose #jesussaves #depression #divorce #churchhurt #relationships
This is the recipe to change the world we live in. Both daughters and sons are watching every single thing. Dads the responsibility is on you.

Pretty big announcement over here at ASV Marketing 🤍 

I am now offering Wedding Day Content Creation Services + more!!! 

Why? 
As a blogger with over ten years of experience, a former bride with mentionable nuptials ☕️ featured in several publications, a prior corporate creative content designer, a former wedding photographer, a marketing expert, and an aesthetic creative who loves capturing pleasing to the eye but also candid magic... why not? 

I certainly gleaned much from my wedding 👀🤍 & want to bring my expertise, energy, passion & LOVE to your special day. About this time last year I had been married just about three months and there had already been so many challenges I’d never EVER anticipated. I was really struggling—missing my family and to understand why situations were the way that they were. It was unlike anything I’d seen before. I struggled in secret from my family and bore the weight that was heavy as I felt things were failing and it was so soon. I was doing my best to perform as expected but that was only a temporary solution. I had always dreamed of what married life would be and wanted our FIRST MARRIED Thanksgiving to be that what dreams were made of. My mom always made the holidays so special no matter what the situation was—which being transparent wasn’t always perfect… Being in driving distance of my family I thought surely we’d get to spend the holiday with them only to find that I had waived that right when I wed. “We were going to be our own family now and create our own separate traditions together”—it was odd because I’d never heard of not seeing either family on a holiday. I tried to get excited about what I’d been told because my mom always taught me to have a positive attitude about any situation but then quickly felt my hands tied behind my back as I tried to make “our new special traditions”. “It had been about me before but not anymore”—we were in ministry now and that meant we were not leaving Frisco. I see now my brain must have been broken to have believed being married + in ministry meant you didn’t see your family or it could have been I was expending all my energy alone to try to save, fix & hold together by shear brute force our covenant before God. But he was going to leave me anyways no matter what I did. I share this because I don’t want the struggles I walked through to be in vain—I want to help someone through my vulnerability. 

This year I walk in so much gratitude not because things are perfect (y’all def know they are not) but because Jesus is making all things perfect in HIS time. My 💔 is healing and that is what I want for anyone who resonates with a season of bitter pain. You are not alone, Jesus hears you. Thanksgiving is a mentality and IT IS spiritual warfare. 🤎

All that I have is a hallelujah 🤍 

#thanksgiving

If someone has ever perverted scripture to you then know first hand how harmful that is. Women are precious to Jesus and are not objects for sex on demand, abuse or UNGODLY control. Furthermore women are not inferior to men!

Understanding the complexity of #biblicalsubmission, it’s essential to unravel misinterpretations that have caused GRAVE harm. In Ephesians 5:22-24, Paul’s call for wives to submit is often distorted, leading to manipulation and control. However, the passage begins with a universal call for mutual submission among believers, eliminating room for dominance. The enemy has been twisting these words and used them to bring destruction to human beings and marriages for centuries!

Christ’s example is pivotal. His treatment of the church is marked by tenderness, sacrificial love, and care. This challenges husbands to emulate Christ’s servant leadership, a far cry from hierarchical domination. In emphasizing husbands’ responsibility to love their wives as Christ loves the church, Paul underscores the importance of sacrificial love over control or violence.

Let’s remember the original context without chapter and verse divisions, urging believers to seek each other’s well-being and reject any form of manipulation, control, or violence. The first directive Paul makes about submission is for all believers to mutually submit one to another. (Gasp! Husbands ALSO to their wives?!) By understanding submission through Christ’s example, we foster relationships built on love, respect, and mutual care. The sinful tendency of many men to either twist their leadership role through dominion & control is shameful to God. I believe it causes God to both weep and rise up in Holy anger. It happens, I’ve seen it & lived it. Sister that is not God’s will for YOUR LIFE! 

This isn’t #feminism this is #bible but yes I do support my gender. 

#BiblicalSubmission #MutualLove #truesubmission #legalism #religion #freedom #cultawareness #bibleeducation #womenarenotobjects #protectwomen #masculinity #christianity

The first time I was called a Jezebel I was absolutely devastated. I felt literally so much shame and locked myself in the prayer closet for hours. I was told that spirit in me needed to break and I was determined to get it done because I didn’t want to be a Jezebel. I wanted to be a good wife, I wanted our mission to be successful and I wanted to be submitted. That term hung heavy on me for months and I would catch myself at every turn of a problem where I used my voice then to be redirected that my Jezebel spirit was still not broken. I now know I don’t have a Jezebel spirit but rather Jesus resides in my heart. I came to the revelation that because I am not afraid to speak up for righteousness even as a woman this was used in an effort to shut me up. I was labeled after a women who was actually vile but didn’t reflect my heart at all. If you’ve been falsely called Jezebel it’s time for you to actually read who Jezebel is and to reject that false label with true biblical backing. 

“This is a term used to shut down independent thinking and acting women that seem a threat to the “leadership” of the church. It’s an extremely abusive application of a story about an evil woman who was not evil because she was a woman with a position of power, but because she worshipped false gods, among other wicked things she did - things not limited to women, but evil characteristics men can have too. For the longest time, I associated it with a woman who would take charge and I shrunk into the background and didn’t want to be too strong or speak my mind or anything that could have the “spirit of jezebel”.

relationships, divorce and church splits. Don’t fall pray to this spirit.

SIN MADE #SUBMISSION DISTASTEFUL not Jesus. 

#Biblicalsubmission is a beautiful gift God gave to women in marriage as a means to protect them because he loves them so MUCH. We can see in the Bible—time and time again how Jesus felt about women through his interactions with them. They were not a doormat or seen as inferior but rather they were loved and attended to with extreme care. (common theme LOVE) God is a gentleman—he gave us free will, he NEVER forces anything on us. It’s easy to submit to him for this very reason. A man who leads well will lead like Jesus and you will find it NATURAL to submit to him. Submission may be triggering to you if it has been used in perverted way to thort anointing, or leadership! God designed the female and he does all things well. All have qualities that God has to adjust, and temper. So there may be times when that occurs, but it will never be shaming - or CRUSHING! Jesus sees when that occurs and will not let it slide. Often in this context you can identify a spirit of #religion is in operation. We know this is not as Jesus intends… why because Jesus is a good father and HIS WORD is PURE. He would NEVER use submission to hurt women. He doesn’t want anyone to live that way. 

It is truly because of Biblical submission that a wife CAN confidently follow her husband’s lead. And in Ephesians 5:23 it is made clear that a man DOES have responsibility for leadership in his home. But again, it’s ONLY as a leader that his wife submits to him — NOT as a tyrant or her superior. Responsibility is to whom much is given, MUCH is REQUIRED. 

Jesus loves #covenant marriage. It is a reflection of him and his bride. He loves to see a husband lead his wife with sacrificial love and in turn her respect and submit to his leadership. 

We can’t swing so far one way trying to avoid male domination that we go to the other extreme and strip husbands of their authority. ♥️

This year, my connection with Jesus has deepened to profound depths, casting a transformative light on my approach to this Advent season. I now contemplate the essence of this season in a manner unparalleled in my lifetime, eagerly anticipating Christmas with joy in celebrating the birth of Jesus. He stands as the paramount blessing, his arrival marking the realization of the promise of a savior from the lineage of David—the Messiah. Reflecting on Mary’s experience, I endeavor to grasp the profound nature of this moment for her and Joseph. It’s a challenge to comprehend, yet a profound testament to walking in faith and serving as a vessel in divine purpose. 

Two years ago about this time my mom and I went back to my alma mater for lessons and carols—a momentous experience. I worked this special event all four years I attended Sewanee as an Angel and it was always so beautiful. These photos came up as a memory and was just another reminder of how blessed I am.

Love is about action, how a person lives for the Lord and obeys him and how a person lives for others and serves them. It’s about a firm foundation on Christ—to build your life because God is LOVE. 

2024 is about LOVE as Jesus defines it NOT as our culture defines it. 

Because Love is countercultural.
